%20say.%20Don%E2%80%99t%20judge%20them.%20Reassure%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%222%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20rush%20to%20give%20advice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDon%E2%80%99t%20tell%20them%20that%20what%20they%20are%20thinking%20of%20is%20wrong%3B%20they%20know%20it.%20Be%20empathetic%20and%20just%20give%20them%20a%20safe%20space%20to%20speak.%20Once%20you%20give%20them%20space%20to%20accept%20themselves%2C%20they%20will%20be%20able%20to%20ask%20you%20what%20they%20need%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%223%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20guilt%20them%20or%20make%20it%20all%20about%20you!%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20tend%20to%20make%20it%20all%20about%20ourselves%20and%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98If%20you%20love%20me%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20do%20it%E2%80%99.%20This%20is%20only%20about%20them%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20their%20distress.%20Hold%20space%20for%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%224%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EAsk%20them%20what%20they%20need%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBe%20curious%20and%20ask%20them%20questions.%20Try%20to%20understand%20what%20is%20wrong%20and%20what%E2%80%99s%20bothering%20them.%20Ask%20them%20what%20you%20can%20do%20to%20help%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%225%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EAsk%20relevant%20questions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAsk%20them%20about%20their%20experiences%20and%20when%20they%20started%20feeling%20this%20way.%20Try%20to%20understand%20what%20contributed%20to%20it.%20Ask%20them%20what%20you%20could%20do%20to%20help%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Priyanka%2C%20adding%2C%20%E2%80%9CSeek